Q3: 

Loops are used to execute a block of code repeatedly until a specified condition is false. They help avoid writing repetitive code.



# Types of Loops in JavaScript:

-For Loop

   Syntax:
 
   for (initialization; condition; increment) {
     // code block
   }

Example:

 
   for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
     console.log(i);
   }


-While Loop**

   Syntax:

  
   while (condition) {
     // code block
   }`

   Example:

   let i = 1;
   while (i <= 5) {
     console.log(i);
     i++;
   }
 

-Do...While Loop**

 Syntax:

  
   do {
     // code block
   } while (condition);
 

Example:

 
   let i = 1;
   do {
     console.log(i);
     i++;
   } while (i <= 5);
 

----------------------------------------------------------------*--------------------------------------------------------------------*----------------------------------------------------------------*--------------------------------------------------------------------*

Q4:


const num1 = 10;
const num2 = 25;

for (let i = num1 + 1; i <= num2; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}


Output:

11
12
13

25



